{"word":"πρεσβυτικός","slug":"πρεσβυτικός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πρεσβυτικός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:πρεσβῦτις'><el>πρεσβῦτις</el></a>\n<el>(πρεσβῡτικός, ή, όν) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>like an old man, elderly</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>senilis</el>, <el>ὄχλος</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>κακὰ πρ.</el> the evils <i>of age</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>old-fashioned, antiquated</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-κῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}